Comment: Completely disagree (with the exception of whitie needing to shut-up), but at least Evita's points are not the moronic ravings of Prof Friedman.

//Which means that the citizens and taxpayers of our country will never know who voted against the presidency of Mshowerlozi. But more disappointingly, we won’t know who voted to retain his services.//
Just refer to the 7 or 8 previous motions of no confidence, including the ones after the nkanadla scandals. 

//Let our first family be allowed to walk away into the Arabian sunset like Idi Amin, to be forgotten, if never forgiven.//
The guy who took over from Amin in 1986 is STILL in power. He's son is in line to take over the reigns. No, we need accountability and accountability requires consequences! If JZ walks, then what will deter the next skelm?

